  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "ONNX (Open Neural Network Exchange) is an open file format for representing trained machine learning models. It defines a common set of operators and a standard way to describe a computational graph, so a model trained in one framework (PyTorch, TensorFlow) can be exported to ONNX and run in another runtime.\nFor on-device inference, ONNX is significant because it is the native model format for NPU acceleration on Windows. ONNX Runtime, maintained by Microsoft, provides execution providers that route model operations to different hardware accelerators — including the QNN execution provider for Qualcomm Hexagon NPUs. Models must typically be converted to ONNX and optimized for the target hardware before they can run on an NPU.\n",
